reviews.review_text:
Outstanding work HS This show kicks butt, right in the heart of Pittsburgh, an underrated Dead city.
Got a great CC Rider here, and China Cat > Rider.
Ton of early Brent energy.
Late 79 kicks butt overall.
The sound is top notch. Hunter uses good ingredients in the matrix.

HS Crushes Another One Seriously, this is getting out of hand. Soon we will all expect so much every time we Matrix and Seamons listed that anything less than a vivid transient experience will get folks upset.. Oh well, its the interwebs & you can just ignore them.

Back in maybe 2006 I wrote a review in which I was touting an SBD of this show, then I update it 2013 because I'm in love with a new AUD. I checked both out and I wasn't wrong. Strong sources for sure. This is better though.

Don't get misled by the set 2 set list. China Cat and LL Rain are kind of whatever, but Rider is hot and everything from He's Gone to the end is smoking.

3 cheers for HS showering the archive with more A++ Matrix.
